This folder contain code for the lidar.
 
This code takes in the scan from the hokuyo lidar, filters it using the PassThrough and StatisticalOutlerRemoval filters.
It then returns directions to center a specified object with respect to the position of the lidar.
It also returns directions to orient a specified object with respect to the y-axis, which is defined by the axis that extends from the sides of the lidar.


To run code, just run the following commands: 
launch runLidar.launch
